item1.title: photography
item1.content: Photography is the science, art and practice of creating durable images by recording light or other electromagnetic radiation

item2.title: web design
item2.content: Web design encompasses many different skills and disciplines in the production and maintenance of websites.

item3.title: creativity
item3.content: Creativity is a phenomenon whereby something new and somehow valuable is formed. The created item may be intangible or a physical object.

item4.title: seo
item4.content: Search engine optimization (SEO) is the process of affecting the visibility of a website or a web page in a web search engine's unpaid results.

item5.title: Css/Html
item5.content: HyperText Markup Language, commonly abbreviated as HTML, is the standard markup language used to create web pages.

item6.title: digital
item6.content: With digital signals, system noise, provided it is not too great, will not change the quantification whereas with signals handled using analog processing.
